title: For Sale:  Rem 742 semi auto 30-06 w/Scope
postcontent:
Remington 742 woods master semi-automatic in 30-06. This gun is immaculate shape with one caveat (we’ll get to that in a minute). A couple minor safe dings in the stock, bluing is 100%. No rust or woods scrapes, I don’t think this thing has ever been hunted.  I replaced the sling studs so they’re fresh and rock solid. Has a Simmons expedition 3-9-40 scope mounted on see through rings. Comes with one blue and one stainless mag.

Here’s the caveat – the gun fires and is accurate. However, this thing has been a safe queen with a capital Q. from what I have read and what I understand talking to a lot of older rem guys is that the 742’s and a few other series were susceptible to chamber sticking if not cleaned properly before storage. As such, this one has trouble extracting brass. If you manually run the action, it will pull it out. When fired though, it sits in the chamber and the next round jams when it hits the back of the spent brass.

It is my belief that a good proper bore scrubbing and a swab of the gas tube would solve this issue and you’d have yourself a beautiful deer rifle. Or, buy a bunch of 10 round mags (under $20 I think…) and have yourself a poor man’s Garand. The little fella needs some TLC. I’ve had the full intention of taking it apart and cleaning it proper ever since I’ve owned it but guess what, I haven’t. I don’t see myself having the time even before THIS year’s deer season. So - I’m letting it go so someone else might get to enjoy it. If you have the elbow grease and the time, here’s your chance.

asking $375. Lower offers considered but don’t be surprised if I sit on it for a bit. i've seen plenty of these sitting on tables at gun shows with no glass for $450 in worse shape than this one
FTF mpls metro area. Not willing to ship at this time. Need to SEE a DL and permit, no shady deals.

would consider trades involving...452 cal projectiles plated or fmj etc, .22 cal rifles/revolvers, holster work, ladders (step and/or extension), bench grinder, shop equipment (some might be long shots but you never know... i might not know i need it  :D )

The GSG-5 is a semi-automatic rimfire rifle chambered for the .22 LR cartridge and is produced by German Sport Guns. In many ways, the GSG-5 is an exact replica of the Heckler & Koch MP-5 H&K MP5 sub-machinegun. 

Ergonomics and handling are identical to that of the MP 5 with an overall length of 33.5” and a weight of 6.6 pounds which makes it an ideal training tool for law enforcement, military personnel and civilians. 22 long rifles offer an immense savings over 9mm/40/45 caliber ammunition allowing extensive range time with the GSG-5 at a minimal cost to the user. 

Barrel length on the GSG-5 rifle is 16.25 inches including the faux suppressor which surpasses federal requirements, making it legal to own by anyone. The GSG-5 utilizes either a 22 or 10 rd detachable box magazine that releases with an H&K style paddle magazine release. The charging handle on the GSG-5 is located on the left side of the receiver and is non-reciprocating just like the H&K MP5 series. 

The GSG-5 comes standard with a conventional MP 5 style stock and forend but American Tactical Imports also offers several different style stocks and tactical forends including a side-folding stock like the H&K MP5k-PDW and a retractable stock as offered on the H&K MP5A3. The GSG-5 comes with a standard H&K style forend but is upgradeable to a tactical railed forend that accepts tactical grips, lights and lasers.

The GSG-5 utilizes the H&K style drum sight, which can be adjusted for both windage and elevation. Accessories available for the GSG-5 include a claw mount with Picatinny rail allowing just about any optic from a tactical or hunting scope to a close quarters battle optic like a red dot sight to be mounted on the receiver. In addition to extra magazines ATI also offers a tactical magazine coupler for joining two magazines together, making for a faster reload. American Tactical Imports also offers an MP 5 SD style barrel/faux suppressor, which looks exactly like the original. Whether you are looking for a low cost tactical trainer or a fun plinker the GSG-5 rifle is a winning choice. 

In 2009, H&K instituted a lawsuit against both German Sport Guns and American Tactical Imports, Inc., over trade dress infringements. The lawsuit was settled in October of 2009, and resulted in the production and importation of the original GSG-5 design to cease as of Oct. 8, 2009. The remaining stocks will continue to be sold until January 31, 2010, at which time all sales of the GSG-5 by American Tactical Imports must be concluded.

title: For Sale:  Chris Reeves Project 1
postcontent:
I had a Custom Chris Reeves built in 2009 for me.  Times are tough so we have to let go of a few things.  This was ordered right from Chris Reeves.  It's a special order Project 1 and as you may know Chris does not build 1 piece knives any longer so the value holds goes nowhere but up.  

Modifications on the order are 2" shorter on the blade

A shallow index finger replaces the serrations

5 Inch Handle

5 1/2 Inch Blade

Hollow Handle with survival items added, one piece knife.

Leather sheath is awesome and the sheath and the knife still get the Chris Reeves life time warranty. 

I do have it stamped M.R.L 2009 it came like that ordered.  My name of course, you could seek someone to remove it.  But all in all this is a great collection piece to own.  My understanding from Chris Reeves from the 2010 Blade show when I spoke with him, these were ordered from a guy in California and only 15 were made with these modifications.  I paid $375.00 for it in 2009. I f this does not sell online I will be taking it to the Columbus Gun and Knife show on July 16 and 17th in Columbus , Georgia.  A fine carry for a solider. When shipped knife will be insured and tracked.
